doc.previous: Its early routes stretched from Wilmington North Carolina northwest to Cincinnati Ohio with numerous intermediate stops Early routes were operated with Douglas DC 3 aircraft
doc.after: Piedmont initiated operations with Douglas DC 3 twin prop aircraft and later added the Fairchild F 27 turboprop and Martin 4 0 4 prop aircraft It started Fairchild Hiller FH 227B turboprop flights in 1967 and NAMC YS 11A turboprop flights in May 1969 In August 1953 it scheduled flights to 26 airports and by May of 1968 the number of destinations served had grown to 47
